RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REPORT stepped to the front quickly from inside, led clear through the turn, put to left then right handed urging in the lane and stayed clear when flagged with the crop through the final sixteenth. SIDE BY SIDE settled off the pace, raced along the inside into the turn, tipped out but ran into traffic briefly approaching the five-sixteenths pole, altered back to the rail, tipped out with a quarter mile remaining, got to within striking distance with a furlong left to run but finished evenly in deep stretch. LISA'S NONNO broke a step slow on the outside, chased off the rail then angled in on the turn, steered back out in upper stretch and finished with late run but could not threaten the top pair. RILEY G was closest in pursuit giving chase to the outside of the lone leader early, traveled in the two path through the turn and weakened in the final furlong. MISS MONARCH BAY chased on the inside into the turn, eased off the rail and came three wide into the stretch and also weakened in the drive. SULTRY KITTEN stumbled in the beginning, traveled near the back three wide exiting the backstretch, moved out to the four path around the bend and failed to menace. ALWAYS SMILING chased outside a rival or three wide into the turn, started to weaken around the bend, eased in the lane and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Report
ENTRY.OWNER: Bass II Perry R Bass Ramona S Dilschneider Adele B and Hancock II Waddell W

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHATALAS set the pace under pressure from DUA, roused past the five-sixteenths pole, still holding a short advantage over outer rival, put to left then right handed urging in the lane and drew clear in the final sixteenth. SCALABLE settled off the pace on the inside, made progress through the far turn continuing to save ground, rallied along the fence in the lane and got up for second. DUA prompted the pace from outside, roused on the far turn to stay alongside CHATALAS, fought with that rival to the sixteenth pole, could not match the winner late and got edged for second. PACIFIC ROSE stalked from inside, tipped three wide at the quarter pole and finished evenly in the late stages. GATE TO PARADISE tracked three deep through both turns, came four wide into the stretch and weakened. MOTET was fanned six wide into the clubhouse turn then altered down into the three path, traveled near the back in the middle stages, rounded the far turn two to three wide and could not rally. PINK WHITNEY threw her head and came away last in the beginning, trailed three then two wide on the clubhouse turn, angled in to save ground on the far turn and was not a factor. LAURENT chased four wide into the first turn then drifted to the five path, remained well off the rail up the backstretch, came four wide into the stretch and had little left for the drive.

Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of A race other than Claiming or Starter 4 lbs. Maidens 6 lbs. High weights preferred, Stakesw inners second preference and third preference to Stakes placed horses. Total earnings in races other than claiming or starter will be used to determine preference of horses of equal weight. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SLIDER set the pace under pressure from outer rival, drifted out and came four wide into the lane while relinquishing the lead to DARK VINTAGE (IRE), fought with that rival to the sixteenth pole and dug in late to draw clear. DARK VINTAGE (IRE) broke a step slow, chased along the rail into and around the bend, launched a bid exiting the turn and took over at the top of the lane, held a short lead over SLIDER into the final furlong, dueled into the final sixteenth and yielded late. APRIL VINTAGE stalked wide up the backstretch, went five wide into the turn, angled into the three path then bumped with inner rival approaching the quarter pole, kept on through the lane and bested the rest. DES DOIGTS was off slow to begin, raced near the back, altered out from behind steadying rival at the three-eighths pole, steered out in upper stretch and summoned a mild rally to earn a minor award. BEAR RIVER chased three deep into the turn, got floated six wide past the quarter pole and flattened out in the final furlong. ALWAYS ON CAY bothered leaving the gate and dropped back, raced off the rail and came three wide into the lane, then improved position through the lane. CHARGE FOR GOLD broke a step slow, had to steady near the inside entering the turn, continued along the rail through the turn, steadied in tight in upper stretch and was not persevered with late. TRANCHE broke a step slow, chased between rivals then drifted and had to check hard at the three-eighths pole, bumped outer rival nearing the quarter pole and flattened out. MYSTICISM veered in leaving the gate, went up to press the pace from outside, got floated five wide around the bend and weakened in the drive. LORD PRANCEALOT broke in, forwardly placed three deep, drifted six wide around the bend and faded. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY INVOLVING THE RUN INTO THE TURN, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT TRANCHE CAUSED HIS OWN PROBLEMS AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.
